A fossilized tree resin, amber is found in numerous locations around the globe. lenders.occupational_info:
I was raised up in a business oriented family in the city of Nampula, in Mozambique.  My mother was always busy flying flitters and preparing rice porridge for sale at our backyard. My father, a teacher by profession, was always focusing at raising chicken for egg production. That instilled a creative and an initiative mind inside me. 
I met my husband in 2008 when I was finishing secondary education. We got engaged in 2009 and we have been living together since then. We moved from Nampula to Niassa Province, Lichinga town in 2010. Niassa Province is mostly famous for agricultural activities and I and my husband got involved in poultry farming right away. I have grown to like the habit of collecting up eggs around the backyard every evening. Together, we have been doing a traditional backyard chicken production – though on a very little space on a rented plot.
We bought our own piece of land in 2013 and started constructing an apartment right away. Towards the end of 2015, we managed to move into our own house. The yard is very big and spacious and we have managed to construct a 10m x 4m poultry shed where I intend to raise up quails for sale. 
I have finished college and I possess a Bachelors Degree in Public Administration. However, my intention is to venture into the entrepreneurial world and focus on poultry farming. My education has helped to open up my eyes on how I could use the public as my clients in the business world. 
My dream is to grow so big in quail production and to even focus on selling dressed and packed quail meat.  It appears quail production is very rare in Mozambique as everyone else in poultry farming is concentrating on rearing of other types of birds other than quails. Quails are advantageous over any other poultries in a number ways: they mature very fast; they consume very little food as compared to chickens; they are disease resistant; they lay a lot of eggs in a year; their meat/eggs are much more nutritious than chickens’.
Since quail production is new in my town, my biggest challenge is to convince people to consider quail meat and/eggs as an alternative to chickens’. However, I have a strong belief that the business will thrive and become a great success as most Mozambicans do enjoy quail meat whenever they visit the neighbouring Malawi.
